    "import networkx as nx\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {

   ],
   "source": [
    "# Class 1\n",
    "G = nx.Graph()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define symmetric positions for the new graph within 100x100 box\n",
    "positions = {\n",
    "    0: (15, 85),   # top left\n",
    "    1: (85, 85),   # top right\n",
    "    2: (50, 65),   # center\n",
    "    3: (15, 15),   # bottom left\n",
    "    4: (85, 15),   # bottom right\n",
    "    5: (50, 35),   # bottom right\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add nodes and edges to make a symmetric \"X\" with center spine\n",
    "G.add_nodes_from(positions.keys())\n",
    "edges = [\n",
    "    (0, 2), (1, 2),  # top arms\n",
    "    (3, 5), (4, 5),\n",
    "    (2,5) # bottom arms\n",
    "]\n",
    "G.add_edges_from(edges)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Draw the updated graph\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(4, 4))\n",
    "nx.draw(G, pos=positions, with_labels=True, node_size=300, node_color='skyblue')\n",
    "plt.gca().set_aspect('equal')\n",
    "plt.title(\"Symmetric Graph\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
